en_6951201_0	Petitions filed over the draft 19th Amendment to the constitution, were taken up once again at the Supreme Court on Thursday.
en_6951201_1	The petitions are being considered by a three-judge bench, comprising of Chief Justice K. Sripavan and Justices Chandra Ekanayake and Priyasad Depp.
en_6951201_2	While some of the petitioners argue, that passage of the amendment will require a public referendum, others submit that a two thirds majority in parliament, will suffice.
en_6951201_3	Several factions made submissions to court on the matter today .
en_6951201_4	The court will reconvene on Monday, where the bench has allotted one hour for the Attorney General to make submissions.
en_6951201_5	The Supreme Court noted that they would present their determination to the President, as soon as possible.
